entry.title: Special Weather Statement issued October 15 at 3:52AM AKDT by NWS Fairbanks AK
entry.summary: Another round of snow and blowing snow will move into the region as an arctic low moves east from the Chukchi Sea this evening through Wednesday. This low will bring accumulating snow over several days, with accumulations of 3 to 5 inches for the Arctic Coast, and 4 to 8 inches for the Dalton Highway and Brooks Range. Winds will gust to around 45 mph from Point Thomson to Kaktovik Wednesday night and Thursday when blowing snow could cause significantly reduced visibility.

entry.title: Fire Weather Watch issued October 15 at 2:11AM MDT until October 16 at 6:00PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD
entry.summary:
...CRITICAL FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS POSSIBLE WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON FOR GUSTY WINDS AND LOW RELATIVE HUMIDITY ACROSS NORTHEAST WYOMING AND WESTERN SOUTH DAKOTA...
.Gusty south to southwest winds will develop tonight and continue through Wednesday, which will bring much warmer and drier air to the region. This system will also bring elevated water levels 1-2 feet above the normal high tide line from Utqiagvik to Point Hope Tuesday night and Wednesday morning.
